<p>The Mallard UI extension provides mechanisms for specifying user interactions
and visual information in Mallard documents. Mallard UI is a collection of
features, many of which operate independently of each other. Certain tools may
support only some Mallard UI features.</p>

<p>The features in Mallard UI provide information about how to display and
interact with standard Mallard elements. They do not provide new information.
All Mallard UI features are designed to have graceful fallback behavior with
non-supporting tools and in environments in which they cannot be supported.</p>

<p>Because Mallard UI provides multiple features that can be independently
supported, this extension defines multiple
<link xref="/if/1.0/tokens#feature" href="http://projectmallard.org/if/1.0/tokens.html#feature">feature
tokens</link> for use with <link xref="/if/1.0/index" href="http://projectmallard.org/if/1.0/index.html">Mallard
Conditionals</link>. Pages throughout this extension specify these feature
tokens.</p>


